        <p class="TableText">Converts the cursor to Hand mode, which lets you drag areas of the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> around. This is useful when you have zoomed in on  <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">a frame</MadCap:conditionalText> so much that you cannot see all of it in the editor. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture,Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Steps/More/Using_the_Hand_Mode_Feature.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Using the Hand Mode Feature</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
